
            Video
            Boris Johnson apology in Commons over payments
            Boris Johnson spoke of "unexpected foreign royalties" as he made an apology in Parliament for not declaring in time nine payments from sales of books he had authored.The former foreign secretary, who was ordered to apologise by the Committee on Standards, said there was no intention to mislead the House and he had been "completely transparent" .
                
                        06 Dec 2018
                    
                
        
